  "original_title": "\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b9a\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bbe\u0bb1\u0bc1 \u0b95\u0bbe\u0b9e\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0ba9 \u0b95\u0bcb\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Kanchan requests to investigate",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Minister of Power and Energy Kanjana Wijesekara has asked COB Committee Chairman Saritha Herath to inquire into the allegations leveled by the Chairman of the Public Utilities Commission.",
        "Sri Lanka Public Utilities Commission Chairman Janaka Ratnayaka, who was present at the COPE committee yesterday, mentioned that petrol and diesel can be sold in the country at a price of less than 250 rupees.",
        "In this situation, Minister Kanchana Wijesekara has also requested that an investigation should be conducted in a Twitter post.",
        "I would like to kindly request @charith9 to call CPC & myself to the CPOE to inquire into the allegations made by PUCSL Chairman on FuelPricing & Procurement. Inquiry should be held on if the COPE & the Public was misled by PUCSL Chairman or CPC on fuel pricing & any other matter"
      ],
